CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 18, 1958, pg. A12, reads: "JUMS - This attractive group of young matrons entertained their friends at a dancing party last Friday night, celebrating the 10th anniversary of the mothers' group.  Seated, left to right, are: Mmes. Jessie Anderson, Anne Barnett, Marjorie Coy, Elva Robinson, Viola Wods [Woods], Estelle Hill and Louise Clark.  Standing: Mmes. Dolores Redwood, Mary Barnett, Eilena [Elena?] Chapman, Corrine Harris, Mildred Woods, Addie Trent, Alberta Atwater, Betty Fowler, Gwendolyn Bates, Geraldyne Mike and Louise Smith. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: JUMS (Just Us Mothers) Club members, seated from left: Jessie Anderson, Anne Barnett, Marjorie Coy, Elva Robinson, Viola Woods, Estelle Hill, Louise Clark; standing: Dolores Redwood, Mary Barnett, Elena Chapman, Corrine Harris, Mildred Woods, Addie Trent, Alberta Atwater, Betty Fowler, Gwendolyn Bates, Geraldyne Mike, and Louise Smith posed in Royal Ballroom during tenth anniversary party
